gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 127, Thunder 123
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Thunder, 127-123, snapping Oklahoma Citys 6-game winning streak. Joel Embiid led all scorers with 35 points, 11 rebounds, nine assists, and four blocks for the 76ers, while Tyrese Maxey added 28 points and eight rebounds in the victory. Chet Holmgren (33 points, career-high five 3PM) and Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (31 points, six rebounds, five assists) combined for 64 points for the Thunder in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 11-5 on the season, while the Thunder fall to 11-5.
